Softmodem - Audio software modem that connects you soundcard with a tty

Its known to work with jack >= 0.116.1 (http://jackaudio.org/)
and spandsp >= 0.0.6pre17 (http://soft-switch.org/),
on OpenBSD, Debian and Ubuntu.

To compil, run "make", that will create bin/sm.

You can use "make withgui" to compil the modem with monitor gui from spandsp.
You will need fltk (and fltk-devel), Fl_Cartesian and Fl_Audio_Meter.
Fl_Cartesian and Fl_Audio_Meter can be downloaded from
http://www.soft-switch.org/downloads.

Read the man page present in the current directory for further documentation.
